          "date": "2014-09-18 22:45:22.000000000",
          "tz": -420
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Christopher J. Morrone",
          "email": "morrone2@llnl.gov",
          "date": "2014-11-13 21:48:15.000000000",
          "tz": -480
        },
        "subject": "LU-5919 build: Make \"make rpm\" use \"make src\" output",
        "message": "LU-5919 build: Make \"make rpm\" use \"make src\" output\n\nWe rework the rpm and srpm Make targets.  The srpm\ntarget generates the source rpm package much as it did\nbefore, but it puts the results in a known temporary\nrpm build tree.  This allows the \"make rpm\" target to\nsimply depend on the srpm target, and then build the\nbinary rpms from the source rpm.\n\nPreviously the rpm target _also_ generated a source rpm\npackage, which could be redudant, and failed to verify that\nthe source rpm package was itself buildable.\n\nFurther the patch moves the construction of the rpmbuild\ncommand line options out of the makefile and into the m4\nfiles.  Scripting is much easier in the m4 where the contents\nare mostly shell anyway, and it also removes a somewhat\nconfusing layer of indirection from the top of the\nautoMakefile.am file.\n\nChange-Id: Id0612ade9f170d84518f01d4e8de654a7ba8af88\nSigned-off-by: Christopher J. Morrone <morrone2@llnl.gov>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b2_5"
    }
  },
